summary: This document provides detailed information on how to view aircraft records, including the types of files contained on a CD Rom, the format of the documents, and the sequence in which they are displayed. It outlines the various document types related to aircraft records, such as airworthiness and registration files, and explains the numbering system used for these documents.
keyFacts: The document describes the structure and content of aircraft records available on CD Rom.
It explains the types of files included, such as Airworthiness, Registration, and Suspense files.
